<h2 class="section-head">Is Peaberry Worth <em>the Price Premium?</em></h2>

<p class="body">For Koa's Peaberry Kona at around $60 per bag: yes, for the right buyer. The price reflects real scarcity (5% of harvest), real labor (hand-sorting at the farm), real competitive proof (multiple award wins), and the underlying cost of growing anything on Hawaiian soil. Buyers who want to experience the best possible expression of Kona coffee, or who are buying a gift for someone who takes their coffee seriously, will find the Peaberry worth the premium.</p>

<p class="body">For the everyday coffee buyer who mostly makes drip coffee before work, the difference between a Koa Peaberry and the Koa Estate (No. 1 grade flat bean, roughly half the price) may not be meaningful enough to justify the cost. The Estate is excellent coffee. The Peaberry is the exceptional version of an already excellent coffee. Whether that distinction matters depends on how attentively you brew and how much the origin story adds to your enjoyment of the cup.</p>

